{"/service/ndnp/gu/batch_gu_cookie_ver02/data/sn89053307/00517177167/1908030501/0757.xml":{"full_text":"T ralh At\nBY THE St\nERALD PUBE P \u2018-\ufb01\n*\"\ufb02w\ufb01.i\ufb01c,\u2018\nEdHtor aod Maoager.\nJSCRIPTION PRICE $2.00 PER ANNUM.\nSR#e =utitied, under the law, to continue all\noriptions until full settlement is made.\nFwA. Rates: 10 cts per inch; 8 cts per line local,\nfo Advertisement, Job or Subscription will be accepted\n~Bm less amount than $l.OO\nTUESDAY, MARCH 5, 1908.\nB e e\nHave you registered? Remember, Saturday\nis the last day!\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nIf you don\u2019t believe it\u2019s dry in Georgia and\nBen Hill County just try to buy a dram.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\n1f the Hoke Smith agitation keeps on growing\nhis name at the convention will create a big stir if\nnothing more.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nAre you for or against good government? Ask\nyourself the question and be governed by your\nconscience at the polls.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nThe announcement comes {rom Savannah that\nall the Locker Clubs have closed their doors. When\nSavannah surrenders then the devil might as well\ntake to the woods.\n2 Pull for Fitzgerald or Pull Qub\n\u201cA Voter,\u2019\u201d\u201d whose letter appears in the news\ncolumns of this issue, comes pretty close to nam\ning the real issue in the race for Representative\nof Ben Hill County.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nThe New York World has not brot out a\nnew candidate for the presidency in several\ndays. Can it be that The World has nomi\nnated all the good Democrats!\u2014Atlanta Geor-\nGeorgian,\nThey about completed the list when they\nmentioned Hoke Smith\u2019s name.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nOf all pernicious vices gambling is by far the\nworst. It robs a man of his natural manhood\nand honor. The fact that it is possible to secretly\npractice it makes it all the mor2 seductive and dan\ngerous When Georgia struck the rum-traffic a\nknock out blow it also hit the gambler hard and\nthey are on the run to get under cover thruout the\nstate. Macon, Savannah, Atlanta, Augusta, and\nother large cities, as well as many of the size of\nFitzgerald are determined to wipe out this pest of\nmorals completely.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nThe bulletins of the Experiment Station, at\nthe Georgia Agricultural College contain a vast\namount of valuable information to farmers. Any\none can receive these bulletins free of charge by\ngending name and postoffice address on a postal\ncard. It is well to state in what particular branch\nof farming you are most interested in, as, in that\nway, the authorities there can keep ycu posted\nalong that line. The mailing list is being revised\nnow and it would be well, if the bulletins are\nwanted, to address \u2018\u2018Director,\u201d\u201d Experiment, Ga.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nA Boost For Fitzgerald.\nCandidate Knapp is having considerable to\ngay about a \u2018\u2018boost for Fitzgerald and for Ben\nHill county.\u201d It is possible that some of the\nreaders of the Enterprise do not know his record\nas a \u2018\u2018booster.\u201d\u2019\nIn 1898 or about that time, the old town went\non the bum. Mr. Knapp had been publishing a\npaper three or four years, or long enough at least\nto give the city a case of the \u201chardups.\u2019\u201d\u2019 Things\ngot dull. His \u2018\u2018boosting\u201d as a publisher seemed\nto create the \u2018\u2018shrivels\u2019\u201d and when business\nwould not give down freely, editor Knapp threw\nup the sponge and kicked the old town in the side,\nghook her dust from his feet and skipped out to\nsome more fortunate city, (that had not been boost\ned ala Knapp). The removal of the blight scemed\nt 0 do the town good. She soon began to show signs\nof recovery. Real estate prices advanced, business\nimproved, the \u2018\u2018for sale\u2019\u2019 signs began to come\n_ down. (They were about as thick over the city,\nEz when he quit publishing his paper and left here,\nas the \u2018\u2018vote for Knapp\u2019\u2019 signs are at present.)\nThere was talk of organizing for the purpose of\ntearing down or stealing and destroying the *for\nsale\u2019\u201d signs that were so numerous.\nProperty values went from less than half a\nmillion when editor Knapp quit business and quit\nto one millon, two million, two million and\n3 half, three million and four million or there\nabouts; now Ex-editor and \u2018\u201c\u2018booster\u2019\u201d Knapp,\n_heard of what was going on, probably he didn\u2019t\npelieve it, but he came back to see, and found the\nol town that he had \u2018\u2018boosted\u2019, into the hands of\nthe harlots and gamblers, booming and flourishing\n_and he has been hanging around ever since to see\nhat he could pick up. He has always been\nready to ride, but never willing to get out and\nThe men who have made Fitzgerald\u2019s pros-\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nCotton started off the right way the first of\nMarch. Long staple is now finding a market and\nsections which raised that kind last year are feel\ning relieved financially,\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Qut.\nBusiness in every branch is gradually picking\nup in this city as elsewhere thruout the country.\nMerchants and manufacturers especially are feeling\nthe return of prosperity.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Outs\nIsn\u2019t it heartless for anyone to remind the\npoor thirsty Georgian that bock beer is\n\u201cin,\u201d\u201d\u2014Brunswick Journal.\nNotso heartlessin Brunswich with its *\u2018booze\u201d\u2019\nship making regular trips to Florida and back.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out,\nSolicitor E. D. Graham, who is at Ocilla this\nweek attending Irwin Superior court, is a candi\ndate for re-election and finds it pretty much his\nway in this neck o\u2019 the woods. He is one of the\nablest solicitors general in the state, thoro and\nbusiness like in the conduct of his office and it is\nhardly probable that the voters of the district will\ntrade him off this year.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Outs\nAugusta is the only city in the state\nwhose citizens can conveniently secure *booze\u2019\nwithout a locker club. If Georgiia was only\nsurrounded by South Carolina, what a glori\nous state it would be for the topers.\u2014Athens\nBanner.\nThe best part of Georgia is surrounded by\nSouth Carolina\u2014and vice versa.\u2014Augusta\nChronicle.\nMaybe, so, but down this way folks think\nthat Florida cuts quite a figure,\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nEditor Mercer in the Fitzgerald Enterprise\nsays: \u201cThe probability is that many Georgia\ncounties will have whiskey candidates for the\nlegislature. They will not announce as such,\nbut by their past records shall ye know them.\u2019\u2019\n\u2014Washington Reporter.\n\u2018\u2018Not as long as the Anti-Saloon League is\nas active as it is at the present time.''Dublin\nCourier Dispatch.\nIt seems quite necessary for the Anti-Saloon\nLeague and all friends of prohibition,,clean govern\nment and clean officials, to be active in some\nparts of Georgia. We know of candidates who\nhave announced on platforms that appear on the\nsurface to be wholly free from the \u2018\u2018tainted-ring,\u201d\u2019\nbut who really are *\u2018running under cover.\u201d How\never, we reiterate, \u2018\u2018by their past records shall\nye know them,\u201d\u201d and the \u2018\u201c\u2018uncovering\u2019\u2019 of such is\ndaily coming to pass and their masks will be com\npletely torn off at the ballot box; or we are much\nmistaken in the great majority of Georgia\u2019s voters.\nYou can fool the people for a little while but it\ndon\u2019t last long now-a-days.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nFitzgerald\u2019s banks have been her pride and\nthe very best evidence of her prosperity. The\nrecord is a most remarkable one indeed, and the\nman who guesses that we have reached the limit\nin growth is doomed to disappointment.\nThe Third National, just sixty days old, passed\nthe fifty thousand dollar mark yesterday.\nWhen we consider that the bank opened it\u2019s\ndoors in the midst of the greatest money stringency\nof recent years, and that it has no large firm or\ncompany but is a bank of small accounts, and that\nit is the season of the year when money is scarce\nand in hot competition with three older and well\nmanaged banks we consider the showing a very\nfine one.\nThe bank\u2019s management is in the hands of\nPresident E. N. Davis, Vice President A. B. Cook\nand Cashier C. E. Baker who give it their perso\nnal attention six days in the week,\nIt\u2019s success was assured from the start and its\ngrowth is a matter of local pride with every man\ninterested in the city\u2019s welfare.\nPull for Fitzgerald or Pull Out.\nFitzgerald is not the only place that is blest\nwith hot politics. There is something doing over\nin old Irwin. Hon. J. A. J. Henderson, the pres\nent senator, is the only canditate for the legisla\nture, but there is talk of oposition to him. We\nhave not discussed the matter with him but we\nhave heard enough to know that the opposition to\nhim is based largely on the fact that he is not an\nadmistration man. Irwin was one of the strongest\nHoke Smith counties in the state, but in the same\nelection that elected Hoke Smith, Mr. Henderson,\nwho led the opposition to Smith, was elected to the\nsenate. That indicates that the people are liberal\nminded and we do not believe they will fail to re\ntuin Mr. Henderson to the legislature if he wants\nto go. He acted in thoro accord with the gover\nnor at the last session and the writer happens to\nknow that the governor holds him in high esteem as\nlegislator and regards him as one of the ablest and\nmost useful men in the senate.\nThe people of Irwin couuty owe him a debt\nthey can never repay. We know whereof we\nspeak.. We have been in close touch with himand\nthere is no guess work in the statement. Ben Hill\ncounty is under the same obligation. Neither coun\nty will ever square the debt they owe to Mr. Hen\nderson. We well know how local issues creep in\nor are injected into local politics, but nothing\nshould be permitted to obscure the debt the good\nold county of Irwin and the good new county of\nAtlanta To Talladega\nEstablished By Atlanta, Bir\nmingham Atlantic Rail\nroad in Connection with\nWest Point Route,\nEffective Sunday, March Ist,\nthe Atlanta, Birmingham Atlan\ntic Railroad places in effect shed\nule between LaGrange, Ga., and\nTalladega, Ala.\nTrain No. 25, leaves LaGrange\ndaily at 7:30 a. m. connecting with\nA. W, P. Train No. 35, leaving\nAtlanta at 5:20 a. m., arriving at\nTalladega at 11:55 a. m. Return\ning Train No. 26, leaves Talladega\nat 4 p. m., arrives at LaGraoge at\n8:25 p. m., connecting with West\nPoint Route No. 36, arriving at\nAtlanta, 11:55 p. m.\nTrains No 1 and 4 will continue\nin operation as far West as Roa\nnoke, Ala. Leaving LaGrange at\n5:45 p.m., arriving at Roanoke at 7\np. m. Connecting from A. W,\nP. Train No 39 leaving Atlanta at\nat 2:15 p. m. Returning No. 4\nleaves Roanoke at 8:35 p. m. arriv\ning at LaGrange at 9:45 a. m.,\nconnecting with West Point Route\nNo. 38, arriving at Atlanta 12\nnoon.\nAll arrangements are being made\nfor the opening of lineof A. B.\nA, to Atlanta. The work on the\ntrack is progressing rapidly and\nwhen the line is opened the road\nwill be well ballasted and in an\nexcellent condition for the opera\ntion of trains. Two passenger\ntrains are being equipped for At\nlanta service, and in point of ex\ncellence they will be the finest\ntrains in the country.\nCOUNTY AND CITY DIRECTORY.\nCOUNTY OFFICERS.\u201d\nClerk D. W.M. WHITLRY\nSheriff W. H. FOUNTAIN\nOrdinary 5 e C. M. Wiav\nCounty Treasurer J. H. GOODMAN\nTax Qollector W. L. SMITH\nTax Receiver EARLIE GIBBS\nSurveyor OSCAR BARRON\nCoroner WM. MCCORMICK\nCOUNTY SCHOOL COMMISSIONER,\nR J. PRENTIS,\nCOUNTY COMMISSIONERS.\nH. M. WARREN., W. R. BOWEN\nWESLEY WALKER.\nSUPERIOR COURT.\nJudge U. V. WHIPPLE, Cordele\nSolicitor W. F. GEORGE, Vienna\nCITY COURT.\nJudge, D.B. Jay\nSolicitor, O. H. ELKINS\nCITY OFFICERS.\nJ. G. KNAPP Mayor\nC. M, WisE Clerk\n0. E. HARRISON C bief of Police\nBOARD OF EDUCATION,\nPresident W. H. MARSON\nSecretary JAS. T. SAUNDERS\nSUPT. OF INSTRUCTIONS\nE. E. TYNER.\nCHURCH DIRECTORY.\nCentral M. E. Church, Corner Lee and Cen\ntral Avenue.\nJ.C. Flanders, Pastor.\nKiist M. E. Church, Corner Lee and Mag\nno'ia Jesse Miller, Pattor.\nBaptist Church, Corner Main and Magnolia\n8. J Parish, Pastor.\nFirst Christian Church, Corner fherman and\nJessan ine\u2019 E. C. Bragg, Pastor.\nCentral Caristian Church, Corner Jessamine\nand Lee. G. A Maldoon, Pastor\nSl S\nU. B. Chur.h, Corner Cconee and Long stree\nAve. E G. Stover, Pastor.\nPresbyterian Church, C rner Palm and Grant\nW. 8. Harden, Pastor.\nT\nCath lic Church, Corner Grant and Suwanee.\nFather Wright, Pastor.\nPR oA\nEpiscopal Church, Corner Central and Main.\nJ. W. Turner, Rector.\nChristian Science, Corner Main and Alta\nmaha. C. W. Hayes, First Readce,\nSometing Special for Meat\nBusiness.\nWe have decided to make spec\nial sales on Thursday of each week\nbegining next Thursday the 13th.\nA special Family Ham small. 15\u00a2\nSkinnd Large.. l4c\nA T R\nA Special 8ac0n............18\u00a2\nA Good B v i\nB\nAndsuch other articles as we\nmay have from time to time,\nGoods sold at special sale must\nbe cash. We have special ship\nments of the finest meats direct\nfrom Kansas City Market twice a\nweek. e\ni\nI hereby announce myself a can\ndidate for re-election for the office\nof Ordinary of Ben Hill county,\nsubject to the primary to be held.\nI have endeavored to perform my\nduties to the best of my ability,\nand trust my services have been\nsatisfactory to a majority of the\ntax payers. Owing to the creation\nof the new county,l will have\nserved only two years of a full term\nof four years, and would appreciate\nthe support of the voters for re\nelection to a full term.\nC. M. WIsE.\ne e ke\nFOR TAX COLLECTOR.\nI hereby announce myself a can\ndidate for re.election to the office\nof Tax Collector of Ben Hill coun\nty, subject to the primary. I have\nendeavored .at all times to serve\nthe tax payers to the best of my\nability, and am running on my\nmerits and the efficiency with\nwhich I have served the people the\npast year. My books are a mat\nter of public record and I invite\ninspection of them at any time.\nWiLLis L. SMITH.\nFOR COUNTY TREASURER.\nI am a candidate for re-election\nto the office ot County Treasurer,\nsubject to the primary, If elected\nI will, as in the past, endeavor to\ndo my duty and take care of the\ncounty\u2019s funds with a view to its\nsafety. Respectfully,\nJ. H. GOODMAN.\nFOR TAX COLLECTOR.\nBeing urged by a number of good\ncitizens 1 offer myself as a candi\ndate for the office of Tax Collector\nof Ben Hill county, subject to the\nprimary, should oue be held.\nRespectfully,\nS. M. WHITCHARD.\nFOR TAX RECEIVER.\nI announce myself a candidate for\nre-election to the office of Tax Re\nceiver of Ben Hill county, subject\nto the action of the white primary.\nThanking the people of the county\nfor their past support, and by a\nfair and impartial administration\nof the office, I hope to merit the\nsame for which I am very respect\nfully yours, EARLIE GIBBS.\nL meeaat i Log Sl e e\nI'OR SHERIFF.\nI hereby announce my candidacy\nfor re-election to the office of sheriff\nof Ben Hill county, promising con\nscientious service in the adminis\ntration of the office.\nW. H. FOUNTAIN.\nFOR SHERIFT.\n1 hereby announce my candidacy\nfor the office of Sheriff of Ben Hill\nCounty, subject to the action of\nthe white primary to be held\nMarch 18th and if elected promise\nto fill the office with true impar\ntiality. R. B. FLETCHER.\nFOR CLERK SUPERIOR COURT,\nBelieving that my services have\nbeen acceptable to the tax-payers\nand voters of thiscounty and prom\nising to do the best I caa in the\nadmistration of the office, I hereby\nannounce myself a candidate for\nre-election as Clerk of Superior\nCourt of Ben Hill county, subject\nto the primary. Thanking my\nfriends for past support and favors,\nI will appreciate their help in the\npresent campaign.\nD. W. M, WHITLEY.\nFOR SHERIFF.\nI herby announce myself a ean\ndidate for the office of Sheriff of\nBen Hill County, subjtct to the\nprimary to be held March 18th,\nand if elected pledge myself to\nperform the duties of the office\nwith strict impartially.\nW. D. HUNTER.\nFOR THE LEGISLATURE.\n\u2018We are authorized to announce\nthe name of Honorable Marion\nDickson as a candidate for repre\nsentative from Ben Hill county,\nand bespeak for him the Joyal sup\nport of the good citizens thereof.\ntf. VOTERS.\nFOR REPRESENTATIVE.\nTo the People of Ben Hill County:\nAt the solicitation of my friends\nhere in Fitzgerald and thruout the\ncounty, I announze my candidacy\nfor the House of Representatives,\nsubject to the white primary to be\nheld March 18, 1908, I hope to be\nable to discuss personally with the\ntax payers and voters of the county\nthe issues of this campaign, and\nwill, within the next few days, sct\nforth my piatform bearing upon\u2018\nthe following important measures,\nin which we are all interested.\nFirst: Abolishment of the pres\nent city court.\nSecond: Abolishment of the pres\nent city charter and a new one to\nbe adopted by a mass meeting BY\nE.S. FULLER,\nATTORNEY-AT-LAW,\nFITZGERALD, GEORGIA:\nagge 1\nThe New Millinery,\n107 Pine Stroet,\nFitzgerald, Ga.\nDR. J. H. MOSS,\nExpert Optician.\nGlasses scientifically fitted. T.J.\nHailes Drug dtore.\nJ. A. REED,\nBuggy Repalrs and Horse Shosing.\nJl5 N. Grant Bt.,\n\u00a7FITZGERALD, GEORGIA\nL. S. OSBORNE,\nPhysician and Snigeon.\nOffice: Empire Building.\nFITZGERALD, GEORGIA.\nDr. G. D. Seely,\nBeulist and Optormetrist\nGRADUATE EYE SPECIALIST\n35 years constant practice. Eyes\ntested, treated and medicine free.\nAll glaces at cut prices. Office\n123 Central Ave. Fitzgerald, Ga.\nD. B. JAY,\nAttorney-At-Law\nWill Practice in all Courts Btate\nand Federal except the City Court\nFitzgerald. Hansen Block.\nM\nT. L. GRINER.\nATTOREY AT LAW\nFitzgerald, Ga.\nBmpire annex Building.\nr\nFitzgerald Undertaking Co.\nUnder management of W. H.\nROGERS. All calls will be\nAnswered promptly day or\nnight. -Phone No 107,\nState License No 122,\nS S S RS P\n\u201cThc Sign Man\u201d\nJust arrived f:om Florida. Willbein Renard\nHotel from now on ready t\u00a2 write signs of all\nkinds. Signs and pictorial illustrations and\nbulletin board advertiseme:ts. DBank win\ndows done in gold leal anywhere, elsewhere\nand everywhere.\nFITZGERALD GA\nFarm Loans Promptly\nNegotiated.\n6% and 7% Interest and\npayable at end of each year.\nRemember, we get the money\nwithout delay. Terms the\nbest. Prompt attention given\nall written inquiries.\nELLIS ELLIS.\nPatrick Bid. Tifton, Ga.\nHOLDERNESS HORNE,\nLAWYER.\nCollections and Court Reporting.\nNew Empire Building,\nFITZGERALD, GEORGIA.\nMoney To Loan.\nOn improved property in Ben\nHill and Irwin counties, repayable\non annual installments at 8 per cent\ninterest. D. B. JAY,\ntf. Fitzgerald, Ga.\nGreat Land Bargains.\n9.000 Acres of Timber at a dollar an acre.\n85 Acres land, 25 in cultivation, good dwreli\ning and out building, 400 valuable pecan trees\nall for \u00a7l,BOO.\n100 Acres land, 30 acres in cultivation, un\nder good wire fence, 100 flead stock eattle, afl\nfor 82,500.\nTitles to above land perfect. Address,\nW.L. WILCOX, Box 733 Fitzgerald, Ga.\nMONEY LOAN\nREAL ESTATE, AXD\n_ TITLES PERFECTED\nTERMS VERY LIBERAL.","height":"28378","width":"20826"}}
